author: Katie G. Cotterill
title: Reader’s Lens: Birdie with a mohawk
text:
Photographer: Steven Bishofsky, Seattle 
Photo taken: Aug. 19, Commodore Park, Magnolia 
Photographer’s description: “I hauled my Nikon D3300 and Tamron 600mm lens down to Commodore Park to finally get a good shot of a kingfisher. Two flew back and forth from one side of the locks to the other for an hour. One finally showed some mercy and alighted right above my head.” 
Katie’s critique: “This kingfisher is perfectly framed between the branches, which makes this frame. The clean blue background also makes the bird stand out beautifully. I enjoy the depth of field that allows for a small bit of layering to add some dimension to an otherwise straight-on shot.” Most Read Stories
